---
import GuideLayout from '../../layouts/GuideLayout.astro';

const toc = [
  { id: 'currency-types', label: 'Currency Types Explained' },
  { id: 'earn-credits',   label: 'How to Earn Credits' },
  { id: 'earn-gold',      label: 'How to Earn Gold' },
  { id: 'what-to-buy',    label: 'What to Buy First' },
  { id: 'glitch',         label: 'Money Glitch & Unlimited Gold?' },
  { id: 'faq',            label: 'Gold & Credits FAQ' },
];

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I get free gold in Bullet Force?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "You can earn free Gold in Bullet Force through: daily login bonuses, watching optional video ads in the lobby, completing milestone achievements, and participating in limited-time events. There is no legitimate way to get unlimited free Gold beyond these in-game methods." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I get credits fast in Bullet Force?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The fastest way to earn Credits in Bullet Force is to play Team Deathmatch matches and focus on getting kills. Credits are awarded per match based on kills, performance, and match duration. Playing consistently for 1 hour can earn several thousand credits." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do I get a gold clan tag in Bullet Force?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "A gold clan tag in Bullet Force requires Gold (premium currency) to purchase. Go to your Profile settings, select Clan Tag, and enable the Gold color option. The exact Gold cost is displayed in-game." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does bullet force unlimited money work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. Bullet Force processes all currency server-side, meaning client-side mods, Cheat Engine, or money generators cannot add real Credits or Gold to your account. These tools are scams and using them risks a permanent ban." }
    },
  ],
};
---

<GuideLayout
  title="Bullet Force Gold & Credits – How to Earn Fast (Legit Methods)"
  description="How to earn gold and credits in Bullet Force fast. Legit farming methods, what to spend currency on first, and how the economy works."
  schema={schema}
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Guides', href: '/guides' }, { label: 'Gold & Credits' }]}
  toc={toc}
>
  <h1>Bullet Force Gold & Credits – How to Earn & Spend</h1>

  <p>
    Bullet Force has two currencies: <strong>Credits</strong> (earned through gameplay) and <strong>Gold</strong> (premium currency). This guide explains how both work, how to earn them fast through legitimate methods, and what to spend them on first.
  </p>

  <h2 id="currency-types">Currency Types Explained</h2>

  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Currency</th><th>Type</th><th>How to Get</th><th>What It Buys</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Credits</strong></td>
        <td>Standard (free)</td>
        <td>Earned by playing matches, kills, daily bonuses</td>
        <td>Weapons, standard attachments, some cosmetics</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Gold</strong></td>
        <td>Premium</td>
        <td>Purchased with real money, daily login, watch ads, events</td>
        <td>Cases (loot boxes), exclusive cosmetics, clan tags, Gold weapons</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <blockquote>
    <strong>Key point:</strong> Credits unlock most weapons — you don't need to spend real money to get competitive in Bullet Force. Gold is mainly for cosmetics and cases.
  </blockquote>

  <h2 id="earn-credits">How to Earn Credits Fast in Bullet Force</h2>

  <h3>Play Team Deathmatch — Highest Credits Per Hour</h3>
  <p>
    Team Deathmatch (TDM) is the fastest way to earn Credits. Credits are awarded per kill and for match completion. A solid TDM session with 15–20 kills per match earns roughly 500–1,500 Credits per game depending on performance multipliers.
  </p>

  <h3>Focus on Kills, Not Deaths</h3>
  <p>
    Credit rewards scale with kill count. Going 20-2 earns significantly more than going 8-15. Use strong weapons (M4A1, P90) on favorable maps to maximize your kill rate per match.
  </p>

  <h3>Complete Daily Login Bonuses</h3>
  <p>
    Log in to Bullet Force every day to collect the daily reward. Daily rewards include Credits, Gold, and occasionally free weapon cases. Consecutive day streaks increase the reward value.
  </p>

  <h3>Complete Milestones and Achievements</h3>
  <p>
    Bullet Force tracks milestones like "Get 100 headshots" or "Win 50 TDM matches." Completing milestones awards lump-sum Credit bonuses. Check the Achievements tab in the lobby to see what's available.
  </p>

  <h3>Play Longer Matches</h3>
  <p>
    Match duration also contributes to Credits. Conquest matches (objective-based, generally longer) can provide good Credit value — especially if you're actively capturing flags, which adds bonus Credits on top of kills.
  </p>

  <h2 id="earn-gold">How to Get Free Gold in Bullet Force</h2>

  <h3>Daily Login Bonuses</h3>
  <p>
    Daily logins occasionally reward small amounts of Gold (typically 1–5 Gold per login or as streak rewards). This accumulates slowly over weeks of consistent play.
  </p>

  <h3>Watch Optional Video Ads</h3>
  <p>
    Bullet Force's browser and mobile versions include an optional "Watch Ad for Gold" feature in the lobby. Watching a 15–30 second ad grants a small Gold reward. This is the most reliable free Gold method that doesn't require spending money.
  </p>

  <h3>Events and Promotions</h3>
  <p>
    Blayze Games periodically runs limited-time events that reward Gold to all players. Follow the official Bullet Force Discord and social media to catch these events.
  </p>

  <h3>Purchase Gold</h3>
  <p>
    If you want Gold quickly, it can be purchased in the in-game shop using real money. Gold is available in various bundle sizes. Purchasing is optional — the game is fully playable without spending.
  </p>

  <h2 id="what-to-buy">What to Buy First in Bullet Force</h2>

  <h3>Credits — Priority Unlock Order</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>M4A1 (4,000 Credits)</strong> — Best all-round assault rifle. Your first unlock should be the M4A1.</li>
    <li><strong>P90 SMG (3,500 Credits)</strong> — Best close-quarters weapon for Elevator and indoor maps.</li>
    <li><strong>Weapon Attachments</strong> — Red Dot Sight, Suppressor, and Foregrip for your main weapons.</li>
    <li><strong>M40A5 Sniper (8,000 Credits)</strong> — Save up for this once your AR and SMG are equipped.</li>
    <li><strong>MK11 / AS VAL</strong> — Later unlocks for weapon variety.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Gold — What's Worth Buying</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cases</strong> — for cosmetic skins. Only buy if cosmetics matter to you; they don't affect gameplay.</li>
    <li><strong>Gold clan tag</strong> — cosmetic, costs a moderate amount of Gold.</li>
    <li><strong>Gold weapons</strong> (if available) — rare weapon variants sometimes cost Gold instead of Credits.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="glitch">Bullet Force Money Glitch & Unlimited Gold — The Truth</h2>
  <p>
    Searches for "bullet force money glitch" and "bullet force unlimited money" lead to many YouTube videos and websites claiming to offer free Gold generators or unlimited Credits.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>These are all scams.</strong> Here's why:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Bullet Force processes <strong>all currency server-side</strong>. Your Credits and Gold are stored on Blayze Games' servers, not on your device.</li>
    <li>No client-side tool (Cheat Engine, modded APK, browser script) can add currency to your account.</li>
    <li>"Free gold generator" websites collect your email, send you spam, or install malware. They give you nothing.</li>
    <li>Using any unauthorized tool risks a <strong>permanent account ban</strong>.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    The only legitimate ways to get more Gold and Credits are the methods listed above. The game is designed to be fully playable (and competitive) through normal gameplay progression without spending.
  </p>

